Slow Cooker Pork Ragu
  --Cook's Country

2 lbs boneless pork butt roast, trimmed and cut into 1 1/2" pieces
2 tsp kosher salt
1 tsp pepper
28 oz can crushed tomatoes
4 oz pancetta, cut into 1/4" pieces
1 onion, chopped fine
2 carrots, peeled and chopped fine
1/2 c red wine
1/4 c evoo
6 sprigs fresh thyme
2 tbsp tomato paste
4 garlic cloves, minced
1 tsp fennel seeds
1/2 tsp red pepper flakes
1/2 c chopped fresh parsley

Sprinkle pork with salt and pepper and place in slow cooker. Add everything else except parsley and stir to combine. Cover and cook until pork is tender, 6-7 hrs on high or 8-10 hrs on low. Discard thyme sprigs. Using potato masher, mash pork in slow cooker until broken into bite sized pieces. Stir in parsley. Toss with desired amount of pasta (yields enough for 2 lb). Serve with parmesan. Cooled sauce can be frozen for up to 2 months. 


Notes: Pork butt roast is often labeled Boston butt in supermarkets. Goes well with rigatoni.
